{"search_data": "Central Agriculture Export Policy 2018 by Modi Govt. to Double Farmers Income by 2022 Cabinet committee chaired by PM Narendra Modi approves Agriculture Export Policy 2018 to double exports & integrate Indian farmers and agricultural products with global value chains, the main focus is to realize the PM Modi's vision of Doubling Farmers Income by 2022.Agriculture Export Policy 2018 by Central Govt.New Agriculture Export Policy approved by the Modi govt. will double agricultural exports from $30 billion to $60 billion by the FY 2022. This would reach $100 billion in the next few years with a stable trade policy regime. This policy will diversify export basket, destinations and boost high value and value added agricultural exports including focus on perishables. Agriculture Export Policy recommendations have been categorized into 2 categories namely strategic and operational as described below:-Strategic RecommendationsPolicy measuresInfrastructure and logistics supportComprehensive approach to boost exportsGreater involvement of state govt. in agri exportsPrimary focus on ClustersPromoting value-added exportsMarketing and promotion of Brand IndiaOperational RecommendationsTo attract private investments into production & processingEstablishment of strong quality regimenResearch & DevelopmentMiscellaneousThis policy will promote novel, indigenous, organic, ethnic, traditional and non-traditional agri products exports. The new policy will provide an institutional mechanism to pursue market access, tackling barriers and deal with sanitary and phyto-sanitary issues.To double India\u2019s share in world agri exports by integrating with global value chain as soon as possible. This will also enable farmers to get benefits of export opportunities in overseas market.  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now  at  "}